description:
Under certain circumstances, code assist eats too much code. When adding a parameter to the `baz` call in `bar`, the code should be `baz(x.x.foo())` instead of `baz(x.foo())`. The code should be changed to:

```java
public class X {
 void bar(X x) {
  baz(x.x.foo());
 }

 int foo() {
  return 5;
 }

 void baz(int i, int j) {}
}
```

Steps to reproduce:

1. Place the cursor after the first "x." in the `baz` call in `bar`.
2. Press `Ctrl+Space` to bring up code assist.
3. Type "f" to filter the list.
4. Select "foo()" from the list.
